 hours I decided I needed sleep (yea I know..wuss).  I came out with a Belt of the Diligent for the time there.  I had a blast. <P>Thanks Pax!!<P><P>------------------<BR>Greywolffe Silverstarr<BR>51st Cleric of Tunare<BR>E'Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Back in the day, Fear was camped almost 24X7, so it was alot safer. People would just run in and shout for a group.<P>I went with 1 yellow into 46, and never had a problem.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tailchaser</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>if you die and lose your level you can be ressed back in even if you aren't 46.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>*point*nod*<P>I started going to Hate with half a microbubble into 46th.  =></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bala quellious</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Remember, Fear/Hate/Sky raids are typically 3-4 day affairs, and can eat up ALOT of time.  Also be sure to get straight in advance how you will be reimbursed for peridots.  You can spend several hunders if not thousands of plat over the course of that time.<P>Also, at least for me, Fear is a big bore.  No XP, No Loot, I go only for guild functions and to help friends out.  Although I haven't been since the patch.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alliliel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Bala quellious:<BR><B>Remember, Fear/Hate/Sky raids are typically 3-4 day affairs, and can eat up ALOT of time. </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Three or four days in fear? LOL. SKyplane, sure, but Fear or Hate? Are you joking? 5 hours max!<P>-----